<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-23T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-23T21:00:00-05:00" n="692" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d692">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">816.00 Revolutions/66: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in El Salvador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MWJ1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">McCafferty</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-23T21:00:00-05:00">January
                                    23, 1932—9 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>13. Department’s 12, January 23, 6 p.m.<note n="31" xml:id="d692fn31">Not
                                printed.</note> The <hi rend="italic">Rochester</hi> and two
                            destroyers have now been ordered to proceed immediately to Salvador.
                            They should arrive in Salvadorean waters late Sunday night or early
                            Monday morning. The Commander will communicate with you and with the
                            Commander of the two Canadian destroyers.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_CWR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>